!!!
%html
  %head
    %title jQuery Mobile Docs - Forms
    %link{:href => "../../themes/default", :rel => "stylesheet"}/
    %script{:src => "../../js/all", :type => "text/javascript"}
    %script{:src => "../docs/docs.js", :type => "text/javascript"}
  %body
    %div{"data-role" => "page"}
      %div{"data-role" => "header"}
        %h1 Search inputs
      / /header
      %div{"data-role" => "content"}
        %form{:action => "#", :method => "get"}
          %h2 Search inputs
          %p
            Search inputs are a new HTML type that is styled with pill-shaped corners and adds a "x" icon to clear the field once you start typing. Start with an
            %code input
            with a
            %code type="search"
            attribute in your markup.
          %p
            Set the
            %code for
            attribute of the
            %code label
            to match the ID of the
            %code input
            so they are semantically associated and wrap them in a
            %code div
            with the
            %code data-role="fieldcontain"
            attribute to group them.
          %pre
            %code
              :preserve
                	
                &lt;div data-role=&quot;fieldcontain&quot;&gt;
                    &lt;label for=&quot;search&quot;&gt;Search Input:&lt;/label&gt;
                    &lt;input type=&quot;search&quot; name=&quot;password&quot; id=&quot;search&quot; value=&quot;&quot; /&gt;
                &lt;/div&gt;
          %p The search input is displayed like this:
          %div{"data-role" => "fieldcontain"}
            %label{:for => "search"} Search Input:
            %input#search{:name => "password", :type => "search", :value => ""}/
      / /content
    / /page
